WEBVTT

00:06.172 --> 00:07.547
YUNIS SABLO: Here's what
we found at the barn.

00:09.673 --> 00:11.589
Tech said Terry's prints
were like the prints

00:11.673 --> 00:12.673
of an old person.

00:12.756 --> 00:13.881
What's happening here?

00:14.339 --> 00:16.214
ALEC PELLEY:
We gotta backtrack to Dayton.

00:16.297 --> 00:18.047
HOWARD SALOMON:
How about sending Holly Gibney?

00:18.297 --> 00:20.589
There's nobody better
at retracing steps.

00:21.714 --> 00:23.923
Sounds like your man
has a doppelganger.

00:24.881 --> 00:26.297
Your van was used
to abduct a child

00:26.381 --> 00:27.798
who was subsequently murdered.

00:27.881 --> 00:29.798
You're a PI?
Make sure to reach out.

00:30.255 --> 00:31.589
HOLLY GIBNEY: I'm here to visit
Peter Maitland.

00:31.673 --> 00:32.923
You'll have to come back
with his son.

00:33.214 --> 00:34.506
Come back with Terry Maitland?

00:34.839 --> 00:36.464
A bunch of detectives showed up
a month ago,

00:36.547 --> 00:38.089
and I thought it was in regards
to Terry,

00:38.172 --> 00:39.297
but she didn't even know
he was dead.

00:39.381 --> 00:41.214
Whatever did happen,
we need to find out

00:41.297 --> 00:43.547
who was working the days
of the Maitland's visit.

00:45.964 --> 00:47.714
You need to call that detective.

00:48.506 --> 00:49.506
RALPH ANDERSON:
What's the message?

00:49.714 --> 00:51.923
He said if you don't stop
something very bad

00:52.005 --> 00:53.297
is going to happen.

00:53.839 --> 00:54.798
(SCREAMS)

00:55.172 --> 00:56.798
JACK HOSKINS:
Whatever you need me to do.

00:57.839 --> 00:59.297
Whatever you need me to do.

01:06.839 --> 01:09.839
(MARIA GIGGLES)

01:11.506 --> 01:13.964
-Tell me more.
-HEATH HOFSTADTER: You tell me
more about those eggs.

01:14.047 --> 01:17.130
-MARIA CANELES: Let me show you.
Let me show you right here.
-HEATH: All the way.

01:19.506 --> 01:23.255
And then... Watch, this is--
This is the beauty of it, okay?

01:23.339 --> 01:25.089
-HEATH: All right.
-(INDISTINCT BACKGROUND CHATTER)

01:25.172 --> 01:27.464
HEATH: (IN HOARSE VOICE)
You're dipping it in-- in-- in--
in the eggs.

01:27.547 --> 01:31.339
-(BOTH LAUGH)
-♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

01:36.089 --> 01:37.506
MARIA: What you think about
them pancakes?

01:37.589 --> 01:40.339
-HEATH: I just like extra syrup.
-MARIA: Mm-hm. (GIGGLES)

01:40.422 --> 01:42.923
HEATH: I like
all kinds of syrup, you know.

01:43.005 --> 01:45.381
(BOTH GIGGLE)

01:45.464 --> 01:48.089
You have to have a perfect
syrup to pancake consistency.

01:48.172 --> 01:51.130
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

01:53.839 --> 01:54.964
(INAUDIBLE)

02:22.172 --> 02:24.214
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

02:34.381 --> 02:35.381
RALPH ANDERSON: Yeah.

02:35.464 --> 02:37.130
HOLLY GIBNEY:
Morning. Check your emails.

02:37.214 --> 02:40.297
I just sent you a few articles.
There was a similar, uh,

02:40.381 --> 02:42.422
a child killing. Two sisters.

02:42.506 --> 02:43.798
The suspect killed himself
in prison

02:43.881 --> 02:45.631
and his name
was Heath Hofstadter.

02:45.714 --> 02:48.297
He worked at
the Landon Senior Center

02:48.381 --> 02:50.297
where Terry Maitland's
father lived.

02:50.381 --> 02:52.798
In fact, the old man
was one of his charges.

02:52.881 --> 02:54.631
Um...

02:54.714 --> 02:57.089
Maybe that was why the police
wanted to speak to him.

02:57.673 --> 02:58.798
Don't you think?

03:01.714 --> 03:02.839
RALPH: Yeah, could be.

03:02.923 --> 03:04.381
HOLLY: I don't think
I'm going to be getting back

03:04.464 --> 03:06.756
into that building
after what happened yesterday,

03:06.839 --> 03:08.631
but there's more than
one way to skin a cat.

03:08.714 --> 03:10.381
RALPH: Where are you going
with all of this?

03:10.464 --> 03:13.005
HOLLY: Wherever this takes me.
Just...

03:13.089 --> 03:14.881
-Just look at what I sent you.
-RALPH: Yeah, okay.

03:14.964 --> 03:17.506
-I'm doing that now.
-HOLLY: I'll call you back when
I have more information.

03:17.589 --> 03:19.255
(RALPH EXHALES)

03:28.005 --> 03:32.881
-(BIRDS CHIRPING)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

03:48.047 --> 03:53.297
-(CAR ENGINE STARTS IN DISTANCE)
-(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

04:00.631 --> 04:05.464
(HEARTBEAT THUMPS)

04:06.756 --> 04:08.089
(CAR DOOR SLAMS IN DISTANCE)

04:12.798 --> 04:13.964
(CAR DOOR SLAMS)

04:14.631 --> 04:15.589
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

04:15.673 --> 04:17.130
(DOGS BARKING IN DISTANCE)

04:34.839 --> 04:38.714
-(SPRAY CAN HISSES)
-(HOLLY SHRIEKS AND GASPS)

04:38.798 --> 04:41.214
-I thought you were a man.
-I can't see. (GASPS)

04:41.297 --> 04:42.923
Well, that's why they call it
pepper spray.

04:43.005 --> 04:45.255
-(CONTINUES GASPING)
-Did you follow me from work?

04:45.339 --> 04:48.798
I-- I did. Uh-- Uh-- Please.
Can-- Can you help me?

04:48.881 --> 04:50.339
-What with?
-My eyes.

04:51.798 --> 04:53.631
Is English
not your native tongue?

04:53.714 --> 04:55.089
I told you I'm not talking
to reporters.

04:55.172 --> 04:58.130
I'm not a reporter!
I'm a private investigator.

04:58.214 --> 05:02.047
Please. I think I'm going blind.
Oh, my God. (BREATHES HEAVILY)

05:02.130 --> 05:05.506
-Do you have any identification?
-Ah! Right side, back pocket.

05:06.923 --> 05:10.172
(HOLLY WHIMPERS)

05:13.839 --> 05:15.339
Get your hands away
from your face.

05:15.422 --> 05:19.547
-Rubbing just makes it worse.
-(WHIMPERS)

05:23.673 --> 05:24.756
(CLATTERING)

05:29.255 --> 05:31.964
-HOLLY: You have a nice home.
-(WATER RUNNING)

05:32.047 --> 05:35.255
ANGELA KELLY: It's called
post-divorce piss-poor modern.

05:36.798 --> 05:39.297
So, tell me what you want
to know about Heath.

05:39.381 --> 05:40.798
You were working with him?

05:42.756 --> 05:44.673
For five years.

05:44.756 --> 05:46.464
HOLLY: The papers say
that he claimed to have been

05:46.547 --> 05:48.547
on vacation at the time
of the murders.

05:49.422 --> 05:51.714
Yeah, he had that week off.

05:51.798 --> 05:53.464
Told me he was going up
to his mom's place

05:53.547 --> 05:55.756
up in Regis, which he probably
did for a little while,

05:55.839 --> 05:58.005
but that didn't stop him
from coming back down

05:58.089 --> 06:00.005
to check on his peeps.

06:00.089 --> 06:02.255
That's what he called
his charges, his "peeps."

06:02.339 --> 06:03.422
And, then I guess...

06:05.839 --> 06:06.923
You all right?

06:09.964 --> 06:11.214
No, I am not all right.

06:15.005 --> 06:17.673
I know they supposedly
found his DNA on the bodies

06:17.756 --> 06:20.089
and his fingerprints everywhere,
but...

06:23.297 --> 06:26.297
five years,
40 hours a week...

06:27.631 --> 06:29.547
that is a long time to work
with someone

06:29.631 --> 06:31.339
and not sense something.

06:31.422 --> 06:33.214
HOLLY: Not that this'll be
of any comfort to you,

06:33.297 --> 06:35.923
but there's always been killers
like that.

06:36.005 --> 06:39.130
Leading double lives for years
until, finally, they get caught.

06:39.214 --> 06:41.839
And, when they do,
their kids and their wives

06:41.923 --> 06:43.756
say, "We had no idea."

06:46.047 --> 06:48.381
-ANGELA: You're right.
-Right about?

06:48.464 --> 06:50.547
It's not very comforting.

06:50.631 --> 06:53.297
What was Heath like on the day
he came into work?

06:55.464 --> 06:57.339
Strange.

06:57.422 --> 06:59.381
You know, number one,
if I had a week off

06:59.464 --> 07:01.172
from that place,
you wouldn't be able to find me

07:01.255 --> 07:02.756
with a heat-seeking drone.

07:04.422 --> 07:05.964
ANGELA:
Hey, what are you doing here?

07:06.047 --> 07:07.172
Are you out of your mind?

07:07.964 --> 07:09.214
HOLLY: And he said?

07:11.214 --> 07:13.506
ANGELA: And that was strange
part two,

07:13.589 --> 07:16.214
'cause Heath is normally
a chatty Cathy,

07:16.297 --> 07:18.923
but that day he gave me
a polite smile,

07:19.005 --> 07:20.089
like I was some stranger.

07:20.172 --> 07:21.839
-HOLLY: What day was that?
-ANGELA: March 6th.

07:22.422 --> 07:23.506
You sure?

07:23.589 --> 07:24.964
ANGELA: I know, because I had
a dentist appointment

07:25.047 --> 07:27.339
that morning and it made me
late for work.

07:33.923 --> 07:36.255
HOLLY: Did Mr. Maitland
know Heath?

07:36.339 --> 07:37.756
(CHUCKLES) I mean,
as much as that old man

07:37.839 --> 07:38.923
can know anybody.

07:39.005 --> 07:42.589
Heath worked the odd-numbered
suites on the B wing

07:42.673 --> 07:44.255
and Maitland's in B5.

07:44.339 --> 07:46.547
HOLLY: Did Heath have
any dealings with him that day?

07:47.089 --> 07:48.297
He must have.

07:48.381 --> 07:50.381
The reason I say this is because
one of the janitors

07:50.464 --> 07:53.464
said he saw him come out
of Peter's suite.

07:53.547 --> 07:55.255
HOLLY: Why would the janitor
go out of his way

07:55.339 --> 07:56.297
to mention that?

07:56.381 --> 07:58.339
-(SNEAKERS SQUEAKING)
-(GRUNTING)

08:10.047 --> 08:11.756
ANGELA: You wanna know
something else that bugs me?

08:11.839 --> 08:14.381
The cops say that they have
witnesses who spotted Heath

08:14.464 --> 08:16.964
nosing around up in Trotwood,
where the girls were found

08:17.047 --> 08:20.130
the day they were snatched,
but other folks came forward

08:20.214 --> 08:23.964
and said that they saw him
with his mom up in Regis

08:24.047 --> 08:26.297
on the exact same day.

08:26.381 --> 08:29.673
I mean, I guess he could go
from one place to the other

08:29.756 --> 08:30.923
and back, but...

08:31.005 --> 08:32.839
HOLLY: What does his mother say?

08:32.923 --> 08:34.005
Ernestine?

08:34.089 --> 08:38.631
-(RUSTLING)
-(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

08:43.089 --> 08:45.130
(BREATHES SLOWLY)

08:45.214 --> 08:46.964
CLAUDIA: Makes a mom proud, huh?

08:48.714 --> 08:51.798
ANGELA: That poor woman said
her son never left her side

08:51.881 --> 08:53.089
that whole week.

08:54.339 --> 08:55.631
And, while I know
that that's not true,

08:55.714 --> 08:57.422
because I saw him at work
that day--

08:57.506 --> 08:59.381
I heard that after
Heath's arrest,

08:59.464 --> 09:01.923
the police were interested
in talking to Mr. Maitland.

09:02.005 --> 09:03.089
Do you know why?

09:04.964 --> 09:06.297
You would have to ask them.

09:10.631 --> 09:12.589
I appreciate you giving me
your time.

09:12.673 --> 09:15.047
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

09:15.130 --> 09:18.255
(BIRDS CAWING)

09:37.506 --> 09:41.005
-(GUNSHOT ECHOES)
-(BIRDS CAWING)

09:57.589 --> 09:59.964
Tolliver Academy in Baltimore?

10:00.047 --> 10:01.798
ANDREA HOPKINS: I taught
language arts and mathematics

10:01.881 --> 10:03.631
to fifth and sixth grade
students for three years

10:03.714 --> 10:06.255
-up there.
-But no references?

10:06.339 --> 10:08.047
ANDREA: It's hard
to get references from a place

10:08.130 --> 10:09.172
that went belly up

10:09.255 --> 10:10.714
after the dean
and half of its trustees

10:10.798 --> 10:14.547
-went to jail for embezzlement.
-I can imagine.

10:14.631 --> 10:16.089
ANDREA: After I moved back
to Georgia

10:16.172 --> 10:17.464
to take care of my mother,

10:17.547 --> 10:19.756
I realized that
becoming a home-school tutor

10:19.839 --> 10:21.839
would be
a lot more personally rewarding,

10:21.923 --> 10:24.214
instead of teaching
30 students at a clip.

10:25.464 --> 10:27.089
I see you received
those references.

10:27.172 --> 10:28.881
Mm-hm. I did. I did.
All these families.

10:28.964 --> 10:30.673
They couldn't have been
more satisfied with you.

10:30.756 --> 10:32.422
I love kids and I love my work.

10:34.839 --> 10:38.047
Tennessee, Mississippi, Florida.

10:39.214 --> 10:40.381
I go where the work is.

10:40.464 --> 10:43.839
But why are all three envelopes
post-marked in Atlanta?

10:46.005 --> 10:47.047
What?

10:52.255 --> 10:54.422
-Three years teaching math?
-And language arts.

10:54.506 --> 10:56.047
-And language arts.
-Mm-hm.

10:59.547 --> 11:01.381
GLORY MAITLAND:
Can you solve that for me?

11:11.130 --> 11:12.255
You think you're the only person

11:12.339 --> 11:14.214
who's tried
to come in here like this?

11:15.172 --> 11:16.673
-I don't understand.
-GLORY: What are you?

11:16.756 --> 11:19.172
Some kind of reporter
for the tabs?

11:19.255 --> 11:21.881
-Blogger? A vee-logger?
-Glory Maitland, I just wanna

11:21.964 --> 11:23.756
-spend a little bit of time...
-Vlogger. Gloggler.

11:23.839 --> 11:25.673
-...with you and the kids
to write a sympathetic--
-Whatever the hell they call it.

11:25.756 --> 11:26.923
-It's a very--
-Get out of my house!

11:27.005 --> 11:29.798
-I'm trying to help you
and your family.
-Get...

11:29.881 --> 11:31.839
Don't you want people
to know the true story?

11:31.923 --> 11:33.923
Because I'm ready to tell it
for you.

11:41.631 --> 11:43.589
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

11:52.631 --> 11:54.047
-(LOUD THUD)
-(RUMBLING)

11:56.673 --> 11:57.798
(THUD)

12:00.214 --> 12:01.422
(GRUNTING)

12:02.798 --> 12:05.464
Come here. Fuck!

12:07.923 --> 12:11.005
(GRUNTING)

12:14.172 --> 12:19.130
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

12:47.589 --> 12:50.506
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-♪ (LOUNGE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

12:54.005 --> 12:56.255
FEMALE DINER: (WHISPERS)
That's Terry Maitland's wife.

12:56.339 --> 12:57.714
Wow.

12:57.798 --> 13:01.756
Screw them. You have every right
to live your life.

13:01.839 --> 13:03.172
GLORY:
Okay. I should go home.

13:03.255 --> 13:05.339
HOWARD SALOMAN: No.
You're not going anywhere.

13:05.422 --> 13:08.422
Here, look, this'll help.
(CHUCKLES)

13:08.506 --> 13:10.506
Gotta hand it to you,
Mrs. Maitland.

13:10.589 --> 13:12.506
You got some brass showin'
your face in here.

13:13.130 --> 13:14.172
Excuse me?

13:16.839 --> 13:18.589
Where are your kids tonight?

13:18.673 --> 13:19.964
I hope you didn't leave 'em
home alone.

13:20.047 --> 13:21.089
HOWARD: You fuck off, Rayford.

13:21.172 --> 13:22.381
RAYFORD BUTTNER:
'Cause you never know,

13:22.464 --> 13:24.464
someone might wanna
even the score.

13:24.547 --> 13:25.673
Are you threatening her?

13:25.756 --> 13:26.964
-Howard!
-RAYFORD: Easy, old man.

13:27.047 --> 13:28.798
-HOWARD: You step back.
-RAYFORD: Get the fuck off me!

13:28.881 --> 13:30.297
-(HOWARD YELLS)
-(CROWD GASPS)

13:30.381 --> 13:32.756
RALPH: Okay. Pay your tab
and don't you come back, okay?

13:32.839 --> 13:36.130
You got a big mouth on you.
You're gonna walk outta here.

13:36.214 --> 13:38.047
You're gonna pay your tab
and if you even

13:38.130 --> 13:40.839
glance back at her,
I'll tear you apart.

13:42.547 --> 13:44.881
-SERVER: Sir, you okay?
-(HOWARD GROANS)

13:47.214 --> 13:48.255
(HOWARD GROANS)

13:49.464 --> 13:51.589
-Yeah, I'm all right.
-INEZ: Easy.

13:51.673 --> 13:54.381
HOWARD: Yeah, just give me
a second. Thank you, guys.

13:59.714 --> 14:01.339
RALPH: (ON PHONE) Jesus.

14:01.422 --> 14:03.255
I'm so sorry.
She could've blinded you.

14:03.339 --> 14:05.506
-HOLLY: I'm fine.
-♪ (LOUNGE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

14:05.589 --> 14:07.297
RALPH: Did she at least
give you anything

14:07.381 --> 14:08.506
worth the trouble?

14:08.589 --> 14:10.589
She confirmed
that Heath Hofstadter

14:10.673 --> 14:12.964
did work there
and with Terry's father.

14:13.047 --> 14:15.839
In fact, Hofstadter literally
bumped into Terry the day

14:15.923 --> 14:19.464
that he visited Peter.
The both of them slipped

14:19.547 --> 14:21.214
on a wet floor outside
the old man's room

14:21.297 --> 14:22.589
and took each other down.

14:22.673 --> 14:26.381
The facility was worried about
a lawsuit, but Terry was fine.

14:26.464 --> 14:31.422
Because, um, you know,
Maitland's wife and daughter,

14:31.506 --> 14:35.631
they said the same thing.
Terry bumped into some nurse

14:35.714 --> 14:38.673
and, um,
the guy scratched him.

14:38.756 --> 14:44.172
-Oh, yeah?
-RALPH: Yeah. So, anything else?

14:44.255 --> 14:46.964
Just one thing. On the day
that they had the spill

14:47.047 --> 14:48.255
-at the hospital.
-RALPH: Yeah?

14:48.339 --> 14:50.464
Heath wasn't supposed
to be there.

14:50.547 --> 14:53.964
He went out of his way
to come in on a day he had off.

14:54.047 --> 14:55.297
And that would've been
March 6th,

14:55.381 --> 14:57.756
the day after the Williams
sisters were found dead.

14:57.839 --> 14:58.964
Okay.

15:00.005 --> 15:01.339
Talk later.

15:09.714 --> 15:13.172
-(PHONE LINE DIALS)
-(CLEARS THROAT)

15:13.255 --> 15:14.589
PASTOR: This time,
I'd like to read

15:14.673 --> 15:16.381
-from the Book of Samuel,
chapter three.
-(PHONE BEEPS)

15:16.464 --> 15:18.547
-Ralph.
-RALPH: How's the homicide
conference?

15:18.631 --> 15:20.297
-I'm too old for school, man.
-(RALPH LAUGHS)

15:20.381 --> 15:21.839
Kept falling asleep
in the lectures.

15:21.923 --> 15:24.005
RALPH: Listen, I was just
talking to Holly Gibney.

15:24.089 --> 15:27.589
And I, um... I need
to take a look at the footage

15:27.673 --> 15:29.923
of Terry Maitland from
the day of the murder.

15:30.005 --> 15:33.964
It went to your office.
Can you help?

15:34.047 --> 15:37.547
You know the drill here, man.
That's a tricky request.

15:37.631 --> 15:41.547
RALPH: I appreciate that, Yune,
but I would never ask you

15:41.631 --> 15:44.839
if I didn't think that
somewhere on one of those tapes

15:44.923 --> 15:47.130
there might be a real
game changer.

15:47.214 --> 15:50.381
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

16:01.005 --> 16:03.714
RALPH: No. We have another angle
here, right?

16:03.798 --> 16:05.422
Will you go to that, please?

16:05.506 --> 16:07.214
(RALPH CLEARS THROAT)

16:12.631 --> 16:13.631
Anything?

16:13.714 --> 16:17.881
No. Now, go back
to the strip club tape, please.

16:20.130 --> 16:21.923
WAYNE: Who'd you say
you were again?

16:22.005 --> 16:23.756
YUNIS SABLO: Just do
what he says, Wayne.

16:30.005 --> 16:32.214
RALPH: Okay, we can move
to the next piece.

16:39.547 --> 16:41.964
I have a staff meeting
in five minutes.

16:42.047 --> 16:44.172
Yeah, no problem. Thanks.
Play it again.

16:44.255 --> 16:45.381
You okay here, Wayne?

16:48.381 --> 16:49.714
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

16:49.798 --> 16:51.130
HOLLY: Hi, Peter.

16:54.756 --> 16:56.756
Do you have something
I could put these in?

16:56.839 --> 16:59.547
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV)

17:02.631 --> 17:05.255
-My name is--
-I know who you are.

17:05.339 --> 17:08.798
-You don't have to tell me.
-HOLLY: Well, that's good.

17:11.172 --> 17:12.673
I wanted to ask you
a few questions

17:12.756 --> 17:13.839
about Heath Hofstadter.

17:13.923 --> 17:16.089
PETER MAITLAND:
Yeah, I remember you.

17:16.756 --> 17:17.923
You were playing cards

17:18.005 --> 17:19.923
with my grandmother
in St. Louis.

17:21.756 --> 17:26.047
You had four jacks.
She had four queens.

17:26.756 --> 17:28.214
(LAUGHS)

17:29.464 --> 17:31.172
The look on your face.

17:34.798 --> 17:37.881
The last time you saw Heath,
do you remember--

17:37.964 --> 17:41.089
PETER: I bet your husband
gave you a sharp smack...

17:42.714 --> 17:44.589
that night,
am I right?

17:46.506 --> 17:50.214
Did Heath, uh, talk to you about
what was happening to him--

17:50.297 --> 17:53.798
PETER: I told my wife
the bedroom was too cold.

17:53.881 --> 17:58.673
So, what does she do?
She set fire to the bed.

18:06.464 --> 18:08.464
PETER: It wasn't him, you know?

18:14.005 --> 18:15.172
Wasn't who?

18:20.631 --> 18:21.673
You know.

18:29.172 --> 18:31.673
He really did fool
all of you, didn't he?

18:33.839 --> 18:35.673
(TV VOLUME INCREASES)

18:35.756 --> 18:38.214
WOMAN: Turn the heat back on
and then get it boiling.

18:38.297 --> 18:40.756
-MAN: Mm-hm. There we go.
-WOMAN: That's good, right?

18:40.839 --> 18:45.130
MAN: Wow. That's looking good.
Yummy, yummy.

18:45.214 --> 18:47.339
Now, I take the eggs
and I'm gonna go ahead

18:47.422 --> 18:49.589
-and remove the yolks.
-WOMAN: Yeah, that's tricky.

18:49.673 --> 18:51.214
MAN: I'm gonna take
these egg whites...

19:20.923 --> 19:27.005
Just play the strip club again
one more time, but slow it down.

19:33.214 --> 19:35.589
Show it to me
from the other angle.

19:35.673 --> 19:37.631
-Frame by frame this time.
-(KEYBOARD CLICKS)

19:43.422 --> 19:47.464
(WHISPERS)
Okay. Can you blow that up?

19:47.547 --> 19:49.756
More. You got any more there?

19:50.839 --> 19:53.589
Okay. Freeze it.

19:55.464 --> 19:57.255
Can you blow that up
on the hands?

20:06.881 --> 20:09.464
Does that look like
he's being scratched to you?

20:38.756 --> 20:43.255
-♪ (STORE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪
-(MAN SPEAKS OVER PA)

20:43.339 --> 20:45.130
CASHIER: Thank you. Next.

21:10.047 --> 21:11.381
Thanks for seeing me.

21:11.464 --> 21:13.714
ANDY KATCAVAGE:
You know, we've gotta stop
meeting like this.

21:15.673 --> 21:17.464
Why do people
have to tell jokes?

21:20.297 --> 21:21.714
I've never understood that.

21:23.506 --> 21:26.673
Is this about your car thief
or your child killer?

21:26.756 --> 21:31.506
HOLLY: Alleged child killer.
And yours, Heath Hofstadter.

21:33.047 --> 21:35.714
Hofstadter? That isn't mine.
That would've been two years ago

21:35.798 --> 21:37.047
when I was still
working homicide.

21:37.130 --> 21:38.422
I thought you were an ex-cop?

21:38.506 --> 21:41.464
Ex-detective, thank you.
Fifteen years in.

21:41.547 --> 21:42.798
I'm trying to get
to the specifics

21:42.881 --> 21:44.839
of a case they had against him.

21:44.923 --> 21:46.047
Hofstadter? Why?

21:46.130 --> 21:48.047
Because I'm starting to think
there's a connection

21:48.130 --> 21:49.339
between the two men.

21:50.005 --> 21:51.673
Well, good luck with that.

21:51.756 --> 21:53.464
The DA's office
won't let you off the elevator

21:53.547 --> 21:55.547
and the squad
ain't gonna tell you jack.

21:55.631 --> 21:57.047
HOLLY: Will they tell you?

21:59.422 --> 22:02.297
-I could talk to some people.
-That would be great.

22:02.381 --> 22:03.964
But only if you go out
to dinner with me.

22:04.047 --> 22:05.214
I'm sorry, what?

22:06.506 --> 22:09.297
You know, so that we can talk
about whatever I find

22:09.381 --> 22:11.631
in a-- in a-- in a less--
I mean, in a-- in a more

22:11.714 --> 22:14.923
conducive setting to talk.
Or we could talk here. Or...

22:15.839 --> 22:17.506
Here's fine. Either way.

22:20.047 --> 22:21.089
(ANDY SIGHS)

22:21.756 --> 22:22.881
A restaurant's fine.

22:25.756 --> 22:28.589
Holly. May I call you Holly?

22:30.673 --> 22:33.673
There's only one thing
that you need to know about me.

22:33.756 --> 22:37.381
I have the strength of ten,
because my heart is pure.

22:45.255 --> 22:46.631
(HOLLY CHUCKLES)

22:48.839 --> 22:50.381
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

23:04.964 --> 23:06.923
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

23:15.381 --> 23:19.089
(FLIES BUZZING)

23:30.464 --> 23:33.005
-SERVER: Here you are, sir.
-Thank you.

23:33.089 --> 23:35.214
-Thank you.
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

23:35.297 --> 23:37.881
-Insvekataj.
-(GLASSES CLINK)

23:37.964 --> 23:42.130
Insvekataj.  Are you--
Are you kidding me?

23:42.214 --> 23:43.964
Where-- Where are your--
your people from?

23:44.047 --> 23:45.631
HOLLY: My father was
from Trinidad.

23:45.714 --> 23:47.089
ANDY: Well, so, wait,
how did he--

23:47.172 --> 23:50.339
He wound up teaching high school
in a coal patch in Pennsylvania.

23:50.422 --> 23:52.172
ANDY: Anthracite or Bituminous?

23:52.255 --> 23:55.339
Anthracite, the blue coal
burns hotter, burns cleaner.

23:56.881 --> 24:00.547
All right, let me guess, uh--
Carbon County?

24:00.631 --> 24:03.964
HOLLY: Schuylkill. I had a bunch
of friends who were Litzis

24:04.047 --> 24:06.172
and their parents would call me
"the tamsus."

24:06.714 --> 24:07.798
"The dark one"?

24:10.130 --> 24:11.381
I didn't mind it.

24:14.673 --> 24:17.673
So, how did you wind up
in Chicago?

24:19.464 --> 24:21.172
I needed to start over.

24:21.255 --> 24:24.297
Why'd you need to start over?
Uh... I'm sorry, that's not--

24:24.381 --> 24:26.214
Because my mother died.

24:26.297 --> 24:29.214
And before that, I had--
I had to stay.

24:30.964 --> 24:32.130
ANDY: You were taking care
of her?

24:32.214 --> 24:33.589
She was taking care of me.

24:41.756 --> 24:44.255
-So.
-So.

24:47.339 --> 24:50.714
Uh... Peter Maitland?

24:53.464 --> 24:58.214
So, okay. So, when the state
investigators found out

24:58.297 --> 25:00.381
that Hofstadter had been
back to work, uh,

25:00.464 --> 25:01.673
one of the days
after the murders...

25:01.756 --> 25:02.964
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

25:03.047 --> 25:05.756
...they searched every suite
that he might've visited.

25:05.839 --> 25:07.631
INVESTIGATOR:
Which one is Peter Maitland?

25:07.714 --> 25:09.339
-ANGELA: He is.
-ANDY: A day later...

25:09.422 --> 25:10.673
INVESTIGATOR:
I need to talk to him.

25:10.756 --> 25:12.464
ANDY: ...they had a DNA match
with one of the girls.

25:17.255 --> 25:19.631
But that alone wasn't enough
to seal a conviction.

25:19.714 --> 25:23.673
-Well, what did?
-Oh, he was all over the bodies.

25:23.756 --> 25:27.881
Saliva, blood, skin cells,
and then came the kicker.

25:29.381 --> 25:31.047
CLAUDIA: Makes a mom proud, huh?

25:35.130 --> 25:36.631
ANDY: They thought at first
it might've been

25:36.714 --> 25:38.381
Heath's younger brother, Aaron.

25:38.464 --> 25:40.172
He had just got out of rehab
a week before,

25:40.255 --> 25:42.005
but the DNA came back,
wasn't a match.

25:42.089 --> 25:43.297
So, where's Aaron now?

25:44.255 --> 25:45.422
Nowhere.

25:47.130 --> 25:48.214
He OD'ed.

25:51.881 --> 25:53.964
(WHIRRING)

25:59.964 --> 26:01.589
(WIND WHISTLES)

26:12.422 --> 26:15.714
(CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

26:15.798 --> 26:18.005
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

26:35.547 --> 26:37.714
You wouldn't believe the fallout
of those two families.

26:40.631 --> 26:43.381
(CAR ENGINE REVS)

26:54.464 --> 26:56.839
-(TIRES SCREECH)
-(CRASHING)

26:56.923 --> 26:58.339
(TIRES SCREECH)

27:02.714 --> 27:04.506
ANDY: I mean, first,
was Hofstadter's mother...

27:07.172 --> 27:08.297
then his brother...

27:11.255 --> 27:12.881
those poor Williams sisters...

27:16.255 --> 27:19.422
Their grandfather had
a fatal stroke that same day.

27:19.506 --> 27:22.172
Their mother tried to poison
herself a few days after.

27:22.255 --> 27:23.339
(WOMAN SOBS)

27:23.422 --> 27:26.297
Uh... She was on life support
for about a month.

27:26.381 --> 27:27.422
(WOMAN WAILS)

27:27.506 --> 27:29.506
ANDY: They finally decided
to pull the plug.

27:31.047 --> 27:32.172
It was like a plague.

27:35.381 --> 27:36.923
You know what we forgot to do?

27:37.673 --> 27:39.547
-What?
-Order.

27:41.214 --> 27:43.172
Well, I'm not hungry.

27:45.214 --> 27:47.881
How about another Coke?

27:47.964 --> 27:51.339
No, uh, double Jack up
with a water back.

27:53.381 --> 27:55.839
-I'll have the same.
-SERVER: Yes, sir. Right away.

27:55.923 --> 27:57.756
♪ ("100 BAD" BY TOMMY GENESIS
FEAT. CHARLI XCX PLAYS) ♪

27:57.839 --> 27:59.172
♪ G-G-G-Good work, Charlie ♪

27:59.255 --> 28:01.923
♪ Hundred bad bitches
In the city ♪

28:02.005 --> 28:04.839
♪ All the girls
They are so pretty ♪

28:04.923 --> 28:07.631
♪ Hundred bad bitches
In the city ♪

28:07.714 --> 28:10.381
♪ All the girls
They are so pretty ♪

28:10.464 --> 28:12.547
♪ Why do you want me?
Are you Annie? ♪

28:13.464 --> 28:16.172
♪ All the bad bitches
Can't have me ♪

28:16.255 --> 28:19.047
♪ Why do you want me?
Are you Annie? ♪

28:19.130 --> 28:21.714
♪ All the bad bitches
Can't stand me ♪

28:21.798 --> 28:24.923
♪ Christ, I opened the box... ♪

28:25.005 --> 28:26.631
See that girl in the blue hair?

28:26.714 --> 28:30.339
I went to high school
with her dad.

28:30.422 --> 28:33.756
Gerard Coover, played football,
and man did that guy

28:33.839 --> 28:35.673
like to put a hurt on people.

28:35.756 --> 28:37.839
Anything I can do for you,
Detective?

28:40.130 --> 28:41.839
How you been? You been okay?

28:43.172 --> 28:45.005
CLAUDE BOLTON: Ralph...

28:45.089 --> 28:47.547
is this what
the cops call "a friendly chat"?

28:47.631 --> 28:49.798
'Cause I've had friendly chats
before and they never seem

28:49.881 --> 28:51.547
to end as friendly
as they start.

28:51.631 --> 28:54.422
I'm not here to jam you up.
Just relax.

28:54.506 --> 28:57.214
CLAUDE: All right, then.
Well, give me a minute.

28:57.297 --> 28:59.839
There, I'm so goddamn relaxed
right now,

28:59.923 --> 29:01.089
I might just pass out.

29:02.172 --> 29:03.255
(RALPH CHUCKLES)

29:08.756 --> 29:11.589
Hey, you remember that night,
when-- when Terry Maitland

29:11.673 --> 29:14.964
came in here all covered up
in-- in blood?

29:15.923 --> 29:17.798
He scratched you on your wrist.

29:18.839 --> 29:19.881
CLAUDE: He did?

29:22.005 --> 29:23.297
Why you asking?

29:23.381 --> 29:25.339
I'm just following
a few things up.

29:26.506 --> 29:30.005
So, do you remember anything
about that night

29:30.089 --> 29:32.673
since we talked? Anything else?

29:32.756 --> 29:35.714
Yeah. I mean, he was only
in here for a few minutes.

29:37.839 --> 29:39.839
I already told you everything
I know.

29:43.005 --> 29:46.214
-Okay. Have a good night.
-CLAUDE: Good night.

29:48.255 --> 29:50.422
♪ Hundred bad bitches
In the city ♪

29:50.506 --> 29:52.714
♪ All the girls
They are so pretty ♪

29:54.923 --> 29:56.464
ANDY: That was pretty good.

29:57.756 --> 30:00.255
Okay, all right, that one.

30:02.214 --> 30:04.881
HOLLY: Six hundred and ten feet,
give or take a foot or two.

30:05.506 --> 30:06.589
ANDY: And that one?

30:08.255 --> 30:09.881
Five hundred and forty-five.

30:10.881 --> 30:12.339
-Give or take?
-Exact.

30:16.255 --> 30:18.631
-What about you?
-What about me?

30:18.714 --> 30:19.756
How tall are you?

30:20.923 --> 30:23.547
-I have no idea.
-(ANDY CHUCKLES)

30:25.464 --> 30:30.339
-Well, what about me?
-Six-foot-one... and a half.

30:33.506 --> 30:35.923
You feel like grabbing
a nightcap at the bar?

30:38.172 --> 30:42.714
No. I can't. I have to work.
Believe it or not.

30:46.255 --> 30:48.714
No problem. Some other time.

31:02.923 --> 31:08.047
-♪ (LOUNGE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

31:18.130 --> 31:22.255
Man comes here from Georgia,
bumps into someone who's accused

31:22.339 --> 31:24.589
-of killing two children...
-SKYE: Okay.

31:24.673 --> 31:27.005
...goes back to Georgia,
and four weeks later

31:27.089 --> 31:28.964
is accused of a crime
just like it.

31:33.464 --> 31:35.714
These men,
they knew each other beforehand?

31:35.798 --> 31:36.839
I doubt it.

31:38.589 --> 31:40.631
Maybe he caught something
from the first guy.

31:42.673 --> 31:45.714
Can't catch murder.
It's not a virus.

31:45.798 --> 31:49.881
No, it isn't, but, um...
if it was a virus,

31:49.964 --> 31:54.047
you'd have to ask yourself,
how did the first guy catch it?

31:54.130 --> 31:55.714
You know, who gave it to him?

31:55.798 --> 31:57.464
Because that's
one hell of a bug.

32:01.255 --> 32:02.381
Can I get a coffee to go?

32:02.464 --> 32:03.673
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

32:05.589 --> 32:06.756
ANGELA: It's called a telephone.

32:06.839 --> 32:08.339
Sorry, sometimes my brain
skips a step.

32:08.422 --> 32:11.631
Um... I just wanted to ask,
did Heath take any trips

32:11.714 --> 32:12.756
this last year?

32:12.839 --> 32:14.964
Anything that would've taken
him out of state?

32:16.673 --> 32:19.798
I mean, I don't know, uh...
first thing that comes to mind

32:19.881 --> 32:22.089
is New York City for a few days
back in February.

32:22.172 --> 32:24.756
When he got back,
did he tell you about the trip?

32:24.839 --> 32:26.798
Yeah, just about how expensive
everything was.

32:26.881 --> 32:29.798
-Did he say where he stayed?
-A hotel, I imagine.

32:29.881 --> 32:34.506
Uh... Did he mention
where he went, what he saw?

32:34.589 --> 32:36.464
I mean, if he did,
I can't remember

32:36.547 --> 32:37.631
having never been there.

32:37.714 --> 32:40.339
Um, you two are friends.
Uh, did he bring you back

32:40.422 --> 32:44.214
a souvenir, a gift, a trinket?

32:44.297 --> 32:48.214
-He mailed me a postcard.
-Do you still have it?

32:48.297 --> 32:50.589
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV)

32:56.547 --> 32:57.714
There you are.

32:59.756 --> 33:01.506
Are you gonna tell me
what this is about?

33:01.589 --> 33:02.714
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

33:03.714 --> 33:06.255
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

33:08.589 --> 33:09.839
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

34:45.130 --> 34:46.881
HOLLY: (OVER PHONE)
I need to go to New York City.

34:46.964 --> 34:48.047
RALPH: Holly?

34:48.130 --> 34:49.798
HOLLY: I need to go
to New York City.

34:50.631 --> 34:51.839
Why is that?

34:51.964 --> 34:54.631
HOLLY: Uh... I found another
quote, unquote, child killer

34:54.714 --> 34:56.881
who uh, crossed paths
with Heath Hofstadter

34:56.964 --> 34:59.130
at the hotel he was staying at
where she worked.

34:59.214 --> 35:00.881
-RALPH: She?
-Maria Caneles.

35:00.964 --> 35:02.589
She was covered
by DNA evidence,

35:02.673 --> 35:06.089
eyewitness accounts,
and I just need 36 hours.

35:06.172 --> 35:07.547
RALPH: What do you hope
to find there?

35:07.631 --> 35:10.339
HOLLY: Her. Hofstadter's dead,
Maitland's dead,

35:10.422 --> 35:11.631
Maria is alive.

35:11.714 --> 35:13.214
RALPH: Do you have a location
for her?

35:13.297 --> 35:15.255
HOLLY: Rikers Island,
awaiting trial.

35:15.339 --> 35:17.422
Her lawyer arranged
for me to visit.

35:17.506 --> 35:20.047
I could be there talking
with her by this afternoon.

35:20.130 --> 35:22.673
RALPH: Okay, I'm gonna
call Howie; he covers expenses.

35:23.506 --> 35:25.005
-(PHONE BEEPS)
-Okay.

35:27.798 --> 35:30.089
TAMIKA COLLINS:
Attention, everybody!

35:30.172 --> 35:31.589
What I have in my hands here

35:31.673 --> 35:35.297
are invitations to my party
at my house celebrating

35:35.381 --> 35:39.964
the christening of my son,
Master Jerome Parrish Collins.

35:40.047 --> 35:42.714
Dress code is semi-classy,
so nothing you would wear

35:42.798 --> 35:45.881
to go bowling in
or to kill an animal.

35:45.964 --> 35:49.839
And gifts are welcome,
as long as it's not clothes

35:49.923 --> 35:51.214
with cute words on them.

35:54.756 --> 35:57.923
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

36:12.089 --> 36:13.923
TAMIKA: Are you mad at me
or something?

36:15.673 --> 36:16.839
What?

36:16.923 --> 36:19.547
I was just standing there
talking at the top of my lungs.

36:19.631 --> 36:20.923
You didn't even look my way.

36:22.297 --> 36:26.089
Oh, I'm sorry. This fucking
arrest report's got me.

36:27.464 --> 36:28.673
Driving me up the wall.

36:28.756 --> 36:33.214
-It's not even filled out.
-I mean, I'm working on it.

36:33.297 --> 36:36.089
You've been staring
at that thing since I got here.

36:37.214 --> 36:40.589
-You all right?
-Yeah, I'm all right.

36:41.756 --> 36:44.047
-Jack.
-No, I'm just hungover.

36:45.422 --> 36:47.673
If you don't make it
to my baby party...

36:47.756 --> 36:49.047
I'll be there.

36:51.172 --> 36:54.589
I will be there. Guaranteed.

36:56.297 --> 36:59.422
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

37:01.923 --> 37:04.464
(CLINKING)

37:16.589 --> 37:19.422
(CLINKING CONTINUES)

37:30.631 --> 37:33.464
(SCANNER WHIRS)

37:37.130 --> 37:39.464
(BANGING)

37:41.631 --> 37:44.172
(BANGING CONTINUES)

37:55.839 --> 37:56.881
Nana Gracie.

37:59.839 --> 38:01.547
NANA GRACIE: It's gonna be okay.

38:19.589 --> 38:23.339
-TAXI DRIVER: Ma'am we're here.
-HOLLY: Just give me a minute.

38:25.381 --> 38:29.297
(BANGING INTENSIFIES)

38:29.381 --> 38:30.506
(BEEPING)

38:36.547 --> 38:38.047
DRIVER: I'm blocking the lane.

38:39.923 --> 38:41.047
I understand. Just...

38:44.047 --> 38:45.923
DRIVER: Miss, please,
I can't get another ticket.

38:46.005 --> 38:49.047
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

39:41.798 --> 39:43.673
DON HARRIER:
Hey, Ralph. It's Don.

39:43.756 --> 39:46.798
We have a kid just walked in,
says he needs to talk to you.

39:48.297 --> 39:49.964
He won't give me his real name.

39:52.964 --> 39:55.297
Okay, what you want me
to do with him?

39:59.255 --> 40:01.673
Give me Howie's address,
I'll make sure he gets there.

40:23.047 --> 40:25.714
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
CONTINUES) ♪

40:25.798 --> 40:27.673
(TRAIN APPROACHING)

40:39.214 --> 40:41.422
-EPHRAM: Hey,
you would think judge--
-RAUL: The giant judge...

40:41.506 --> 40:42.631
-FLORIDA: Hey.
-RAUL: Hey.

40:42.714 --> 40:44.172
FLORIDA: When are you gonna
take me out dancing?

40:44.255 --> 40:46.089
(CHUCKLES) Wait a minute.
He can't dance.

40:46.172 --> 40:47.673
-No?
-I'm the brother with the moves.

40:47.756 --> 40:49.130
-Oh! (GIGGLES)
-You wanna go with me.

40:49.214 --> 40:50.923
Brother, come one.
Forget dancing.

40:51.005 --> 40:53.130
How about I take you out
for a nice lobster dinner

40:53.214 --> 40:55.381
and maybe afterwards
we go shopping, huh?

40:55.464 --> 40:57.089
-Shopping for a wedding ring?
-Whoa.

40:57.172 --> 40:59.297
-RAUL: Maybe.
-FLORIDA: All right.
Don't tease me.

40:59.381 --> 41:01.422
-I won't tease you.
-(EPHRAM LAUGHS)

41:01.506 --> 41:03.089
-I'm in love.
-You can't afford a ring.

41:03.172 --> 41:04.339
Don't tell her that.

41:39.047 --> 41:41.172
(SEAGULL CAWS)

41:43.255 --> 41:46.881
(PLANE FLIES OVERHEAD)

41:51.214 --> 41:54.089
(MAN SPEAKS IN SPANISH)

41:57.255 --> 41:59.297
(DOOR OPENS)

41:59.381 --> 42:01.005
FEMALE OFFICER:
Keep it moving, ladies.

42:01.089 --> 42:04.172
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

42:04.255 --> 42:07.130
MALE OFFICER: ...report to
the visitors' entrance...

42:17.047 --> 42:18.089
MARIA: You first.

42:18.881 --> 42:20.172
My name's Holly Gibney.

42:20.255 --> 42:22.339
MARIA: I hear you're some kind
of investigator from Michigan.

42:22.422 --> 42:23.589
That I got.

42:23.673 --> 42:27.714
Ohio, well, Chicago. Working
on a murder in Ohio. Dayton.

42:28.964 --> 42:31.130
My lawyer said you know
something about me and that boy

42:31.214 --> 42:34.923
I never touched, never met,
never saw a day in my life.

42:35.005 --> 42:38.756
-I might.
-You might?

42:38.839 --> 42:42.631
Jesus Christ, I would set myself
on fire before I hurt a child.

42:48.339 --> 42:49.589
-Is he--
-No.

42:50.255 --> 42:52.047
Do you recognize him?

42:52.130 --> 42:53.631
-Maybe.
-He was staying at a hotel

42:53.714 --> 42:55.172
you were working at in February.

42:55.255 --> 42:56.547
MARIA: So were a dozen
other people.

42:56.631 --> 42:57.798
He said he met a girl.

42:58.839 --> 43:01.172
-Was it you?
-I worked the lounge.

43:01.255 --> 43:03.172
You know how many guys hit on me
a night?

43:03.964 --> 43:05.172
Just look again.

43:06.297 --> 43:07.297
Take your time.

43:11.964 --> 43:15.214
MARIA: I don't know.
There was this one guy.

43:15.297 --> 43:17.255
He looks kinda like him.
He kept trying to get me

43:17.339 --> 43:19.130
to go out with him.
You know, like the kinda guy

43:19.214 --> 43:21.422
that keeps going at it
until you wanna beg for mercy.

43:21.506 --> 43:23.214
So, I told him I would meet him
for breakfast

43:23.297 --> 43:26.756
just to get him to stop asking.
I'm not even into guys.

43:26.839 --> 43:29.381
Next morning, I changed my mind,
blew him off.

43:48.422 --> 43:50.339
(PANTING)

44:12.923 --> 44:14.547
MARIA: For all I know,
he's still sitting there,

44:14.631 --> 44:16.673
waiting for me to show up.

44:16.756 --> 44:19.297
-Why, what about him?
-His name is Heath Hofstadter.

44:19.381 --> 44:22.923
He was arrested for the torture
and murder of two young girls...

44:23.005 --> 44:24.714
in Ohio, last month.

44:26.547 --> 44:27.839
What's that got to do with me?

44:27.923 --> 44:29.005
(DOOR SLAMS)

44:32.005 --> 44:35.381
He didn't do it.
He was innocent.

44:35.464 --> 44:38.339
Everyone in this goddam place
is innocent. Just ask.

44:38.422 --> 44:42.297
No. He was innocent like you.
They found his DNA on the bodies

44:42.381 --> 44:44.381
just like they found yours
on the boy,

44:44.464 --> 44:46.339
and there were witnesses
who put him with the girls

44:46.422 --> 44:48.005
just like they were witnesses
who fingered you.

44:48.089 --> 44:49.172
Then how is he innocent?

44:49.255 --> 44:51.464
Because just like you,
there were other witnesses

44:51.547 --> 44:53.756
who placed him in another town
the day of the murders.

44:53.839 --> 44:55.214
Yeah, I was in Newark
with my cousin,

44:55.297 --> 44:57.964
she took video and everything.
They didn't care.

44:58.047 --> 45:00.214
He had no criminal record.
No psychiatric history.

45:00.297 --> 45:03.631
Until he was arrested,
not one of them had a clue

45:03.714 --> 45:04.673
that he could do such a thing.

45:04.756 --> 45:06.506
You ask anyone in the PJs
about me,

45:06.589 --> 45:09.005
I never missed a day of work
or a day of school.

45:09.089 --> 45:11.172
I went to St. Raymonds
with my grandma

45:11.255 --> 45:14.047
every week right up until
the day I was arrested.

45:14.130 --> 45:17.005
I didn't kill that poor boy.
I didn't kill anybody.

45:17.089 --> 45:18.547
I am in this place because,
for some reason,

45:18.631 --> 45:21.255
God wants me here.
It's not for me or anybody else

45:21.339 --> 45:23.631
to know his will, but as long
as I keep him close...

45:31.714 --> 45:36.214
You said "was."
What happened to him? He dead?

45:36.297 --> 45:37.839
He killed himself in prison.

45:39.673 --> 45:41.255
My grandma thought
something like that

45:41.339 --> 45:44.381
was gonna happen to me too.
When I first got here,

45:44.464 --> 45:47.172
these women around here
tried to get at me.

45:47.255 --> 45:49.297
But I grew up with
five brothers, three uncles,

45:49.381 --> 45:51.798
and one father,
and none of them was angels,

45:51.881 --> 45:55.255
so... these bitches learned
real quick to leave me be.

45:57.798 --> 46:00.047
You know about what happened
to my uncle and my father?

46:00.756 --> 46:03.839
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

46:09.923 --> 46:13.047
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(GLASSES CLINKING)

46:18.714 --> 46:20.506
You're family
with Maria Caneles?

46:22.839 --> 46:25.673
-She's my daughter.
-My niece.

46:27.005 --> 46:29.673
I'm the grandfather
of the little boy she killed.

46:30.756 --> 46:32.839
(PATRONS SCREAMING, SHOUTING)

46:45.673 --> 46:47.839
MARIA: They wouldn't even let me
go to the funeral.

46:47.923 --> 46:49.381
HOLLY: I know.

46:49.464 --> 46:51.464
I'm innocent,
just like they were.

46:51.547 --> 46:52.673
I know that, too.

46:55.714 --> 46:57.339
(BUZZER SOUNDS)

46:57.422 --> 46:59.005
Look, I can't tell you anything
else about this guy

46:59.089 --> 47:02.214
'cause I never saw him again,
but... (SNIFFLES)

47:02.297 --> 47:03.339
...if what happened to me

47:03.422 --> 47:04.964
happened to him,
then you are right,

47:05.047 --> 47:07.756
-he didn't do it.
-Do you have any idea who did?

47:07.839 --> 47:09.714
FEMALE OFFICER:
Let's go. Let's wrap it up.

47:10.464 --> 47:11.547
You know, don't you?

47:14.714 --> 47:16.881
If I say his name,
they will send me

47:16.964 --> 47:18.631
right from here
to a mental hospital.

47:18.714 --> 47:20.047
Maria,
please let me help you.

47:20.130 --> 47:22.464
You can't help me. No one can.

47:23.506 --> 47:26.422
Because what he does
can never be undone.

47:43.923 --> 47:45.089
(DOOR SLAMS)

47:53.047 --> 47:54.547
MERLIN CASSIDY: I came here
because I lied to you

47:54.631 --> 47:57.673
the last time we talked,
and it's been bothering me

47:57.756 --> 48:01.631
-ever since.
-Okay. You lied to us about...

48:03.714 --> 48:06.964
I knew that parking lot
because I left the van there.

48:09.172 --> 48:10.214
Okay.

48:10.297 --> 48:12.756
And I didn't tell you
about the man who took it.

48:13.422 --> 48:15.506
Okay.

48:15.589 --> 48:20.422
-I was too scared to tell you.
-Scared of being in trouble?

48:20.506 --> 48:22.130
No, I was scared of him.

48:23.297 --> 48:24.881
He caught me looking at him
and I was afraid

48:24.964 --> 48:26.214
he'd do something to me.

48:26.297 --> 48:29.172
Did he say anything to you?
Run after you?

48:29.255 --> 48:32.756
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

48:32.839 --> 48:35.005
(RAIN POURS)

48:39.214 --> 48:40.631
MERLIN: He didn't have to.

48:42.714 --> 48:43.631
RALPH: Hey, Merlin,

48:43.714 --> 48:45.839
can you describe
what he looked like, or...

48:51.881 --> 48:57.297
Um... You could, um...
could try to draw him.

48:57.381 --> 49:03.047
How's that? Care to try that?
Okay. Good man.

49:16.214 --> 49:21.047
-(DOGS BARKING)
-(DISTANT POLICE SIREN WAILS)

50:03.089 --> 50:04.214
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

50:09.589 --> 50:10.631
(DOOR OPENS)

50:14.255 --> 50:15.756
(DOOR SLAMS)

50:18.464 --> 50:20.422
IDILYS CASTRO:
You should listen to her.

50:22.255 --> 50:24.005
HOLLY: Maria Caneles?

50:24.089 --> 50:27.005
IDILYS: Whatever her name is.
You can't help her.

50:27.089 --> 50:28.923
You don't even know her.

50:29.005 --> 50:32.214
IDILYS: Doesn't matter. I heard
what she was trying to tell you

50:32.297 --> 50:35.005
and I thought maybe you needed
some help to understand it.

50:35.089 --> 50:37.839
HOLLY: What I do know
is that Maria is innocent. Why?

50:37.923 --> 50:39.255
Because there are two
others--

50:39.339 --> 50:43.339
-Holly! Do you believe in God?
-Of course.

50:43.422 --> 50:46.839
-He's the explanation.
-Explanation for what?

50:46.923 --> 50:49.381
For, uh, everything in this
world that ever happened to me

50:49.464 --> 50:52.089
that I don't understand,
that I never will.

50:52.172 --> 50:54.923
-And the devil?
-What about him?

50:55.005 --> 50:57.214
Do you believe he exists?

50:57.297 --> 50:59.589
Well, if I believe in God,
I guess I do.

50:59.673 --> 51:02.839
Well, no, I definitely do.

51:02.923 --> 51:05.631
-One devil or many?
-Many.

51:05.714 --> 51:09.547
Right. How do I know you're not
one of them?

51:09.631 --> 51:12.756
A devil? (CHUCKLES) Um... Uh...

51:12.839 --> 51:14.798
Do you need to see
my driver's license?

51:18.339 --> 51:22.422
When you were a child,
who were you told would come

51:22.506 --> 51:26.714
for you if you misbehaved,
if you didn't go to sleep?

51:26.798 --> 51:32.714
Uh... Jumbee.
My great grandmother was from--

51:32.798 --> 51:36.923
The old country.
For me, in Cuba,

51:37.005 --> 51:40.839
I was told El Cuco would come.
My grandmother,

51:40.923 --> 51:43.130
when she was a child,
was told the same.

51:44.506 --> 51:46.798
Her grandmother,
before they left Spain,

51:46.881 --> 51:48.964
was told the same.

51:49.047 --> 51:52.297
Back, and back,
and back it goes.

51:56.923 --> 52:00.798
(POLICE SIREN WAILS
IN DISTANCE)

52:00.881 --> 52:01.923
El Cuco?

52:02.005 --> 52:05.339
♪ Duérmete niño
Duérmete ya ♪

52:05.422 --> 52:08.756
♪ Que viene El Cuco
Y te comerá ♪

52:08.839 --> 52:13.339
Uh... Sleep child, sleep now...

52:14.547 --> 52:17.506
♪ Else Cuco comes
And eats you ♪

52:20.881 --> 52:24.589
El Cuco, Jumbee,
met an old Russian woman once

52:24.673 --> 52:26.297
who called hers Baba Yaga.

52:26.381 --> 52:28.464
-Uh... The Boogeyman.
-If you like.

52:28.547 --> 52:31.422
All the old cultures,
we had the bad habit

52:31.506 --> 52:34.464
of turning truth
into fairy tales.

52:34.547 --> 52:38.547
When we tell our children
about El Cuco, we say,

52:38.631 --> 52:42.589
"If you misbehave, it'll take
you away and eat you."

52:42.673 --> 52:44.047
What we should tell them is,

52:44.130 --> 52:48.589
"It doesn't matter either way;
it takes what it wants."

52:50.631 --> 52:53.964
You-- You keep saying "it."

52:54.047 --> 52:58.714
It can look like a person
if it needs to be, but it's not.

52:59.422 --> 53:00.547
It's not?

53:01.756 --> 53:03.047
IDIYLS: This day and age,

53:03.130 --> 53:06.673
we find it so difficult
to believe in anything

53:06.756 --> 53:07.923
that we can't explain.

53:09.422 --> 53:11.589
-Not me.
-Not you?

53:14.923 --> 53:17.422
The woman you visited...

53:17.506 --> 53:20.756
I heard her say that her father
and uncle were killed.

53:20.839 --> 53:23.172
Was this before or after
the child was murdered?

53:23.255 --> 53:24.923
A few weeks after
she was arrested.

53:25.005 --> 53:27.714
And the little boy,
who else in his family has died

53:27.798 --> 53:30.130
-since they found him?
-His mother.

53:31.464 --> 53:32.464
Why?

53:35.005 --> 53:39.047
Because it is also known
as El Glotón Para Dolor.

53:39.130 --> 53:43.881
The Grief Eater.
It takes the child itself.

53:43.964 --> 53:46.255
But after, it likes to linger,

53:46.339 --> 53:50.798
because it craves the pain
of the ones left behind.

53:50.881 --> 53:55.089
If the child is its meal,
the suffering of the family

53:55.172 --> 53:56.673
is its dessert.

54:00.047 --> 54:03.964
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

54:07.714 --> 54:10.506
I'm not a good drawer,
but here you go.

54:41.339 --> 54:44.297
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

55:17.839 --> 55:19.673
(SCREECHING)

56:15.964 --> 56:19.214
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

59:21.130 --> 59:22.130
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

59:22.839 --> 59:23.923
What?

59:24.339 --> 59:25.339
What?!

59:25.964 --> 59:27.589
What is happening to me?!

59:27.798 --> 59:30.297
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING)

59:33.130 --> 59:34.839
HOLLY GIBNEY: Heath Hofstadter
never laid a hand

59:34.923 --> 59:35.798
on those girls.

59:36.047 --> 59:38.339
And-- And Terry Maitland
didn't go near that boy.

59:39.673 --> 59:40.756
JACK HOSKINS:
If you give me a chance

59:40.839 --> 59:41.798
to come on board,

59:41.881 --> 59:43.547
I'll show you
what an asset I could be.

59:43.631 --> 59:45.506
What can you tell me
about the barn that night?

59:45.589 --> 59:46.506
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

59:46.589 --> 59:47.839
Okay,
so tell me what I'm looking at.

59:47.923 --> 59:49.714
-GIBNEY: Looking for.
-RALPH ANDERSON: For.

59:49.923 --> 59:51.881
Looking for.
What am I looking for?

59:51.964 --> 59:53.422
-Hiding places.
-RALPH: For who?

59:53.506 --> 59:55.381
GIBNEY: Could be a who.
More likely, a what.

59:55.464 --> 59:58.172
JEANNIE ANDERSON:
I think you should drop
the investigation.

1:00:01.714 --> 1:00:02.673
(GLASS BREAKS)

1:00:03.547 --> 1:00:05.130
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
